This song was inspired by all our memories we have from our school, from every word to every instrument we were overwhelmed while making this one as it kept taking us back to our childhood and our friends. Friends are the family that we choose and we are happy to have a big family comprising all of you and more. 

This one is really special to us as it is an open letter to all of our friends out there and to you. We would love for you to tag your friends in the comment section to let them know you love them. It is never to late to let someone know you care for them. 

And a huge thank you to all the people involved in making this song and video happen, we loved making this song and it was an even bigger pleasure working with all of you

latestPosts.caption:
Six months ago, we released another EP/small album comprising four heartbreak songs. You all showered it with love! While it didn’t reach the masses, it resonated deeply with the listeners it did get to. Each track found its audience, and we were surprised by the equally positive responses. However, despite creating some fun tracks, the songs from our 1st EP being all sad, created a stereotype for us: that we only make sad music.
We had one fun song lined up for release, but then we decided one wasn’t enough. We wanted to experiment and make a statement that KhoslaRaghu isn’t just about post-breakup sad romantic music; it’s anything that we like. We’re always open to new sounds and exploring new spaces. And that’s how ‘Aawara’ was made. ‘Aawara’ is all yours stream it, download it, cover it share it with your friends, we will be in your feed promoting it through the next month ♥️🫂
